 {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 140}, "passed": true}}, "text": "USSR: The Soviet gold sales which began on the London\nmarket in mid-March, and which,\namounted to $47,000,000 between 15 and 27 March,\nhave now been expanded to include the Paris market as well.\nTotal sales during the period 15 March -\n10 April, may have reached as\nhigh as $156,750,000. This is the largest amount of Soviet gold\nsold in such a short period and could presage sales for the year\nfar in excess of the recent annual average of about $200,000,000.\nSales of this magnitude are still consonant with the Soviet Un-\nion's own growing foreign trade imbalances. Increased imports-\nlargely industrial equipment-from Western Europe and the\nsterling area have resulted in a shift of Moscow's trade balance\nwith these areas from an export surplus in 1958 to an import\nsurplus in 1960", "token_count": 140, "token_end_0based": 240, "token_start_0based": 101, "token_text": "ussr the soviet gold sales which began on the london market in mid-march and which amounted to 47 000 000 between 15 and 27 march have now been expanded to include the paris market as well total sales during the period 15 march 10 april may have reached as high as 156 750 000 this is the largest amount of soviet gold sold in such a short period and could presage sales for the year far in excess of the recent annual average of about 200 000 000 sales of this magnitude are still consonant with the soviet un ion's own growing foreign trade imbalances increased imports largely industrial equipment-from western europe and the sterling area have resulted in a shift of moscow's trade balance with these areas from an export surplus in 1958 to an import surplus in 1960", "unred_source_page": 12}
